{"id":10208,"date":"2021-04-09T20:47:52","date_gmt":"2021-04-09T20:47:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?p=10208"},"modified":"2021-04-09T20:47:54","modified_gmt":"2021-04-09T20:47:54","slug":"containers-versus-virtual-machines-why-containers-are-the-winner","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/04\/09\/containers-versus-virtual-machines-why-containers-are-the-winner\/","title":{"rendered":"Containers versus Virtual Machines: Why Containers are The Winner"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349994\">Containers versus Virtual Machines: Why Containers are the Winner<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349995\">Introduction<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349996\">What Is A Virtual Machine (VM)<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349997\">Challenges Of VM (Virtual Machine)<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349998\">Advantage of Containers<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65349999\">3 Key Benefits of Containers<\/a><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"#_Toc65350000\">Summary<\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc65349994\"><\/a>Containers versus Virtual Machines: Why Containers Are the Winner<\/h1>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65349995\"><\/a>Introduction<\/h2>\n<p>Welcome to Module 3 of Lesson 1. This is an in-depth insight into Containers versus Virtual Machine. The module plays an important role in your understanding of <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-gb\/documentation\/\">Application Modernization and Containers<\/a>. I design this course and I have applied some of my knowledge and expertise in the arena of Microsoft\u2019s <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2020\/09\/02\/azure-kubernetes-service-aks-deep-dive-free-course\/\">Azure Kubernetes Service<\/a> (AKS).<\/p>\n<div class=\"ast-oembed-container\" style=\"height: 100%;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Container vs. Virtual Machine [AKSDD Lesson 3 - Module 1]\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/5hEHQfMFGrI?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe><\/div>\n<p>First, let\u2019s take a look at what exactly is a Virtual Machine.<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65349996\"><\/a>What is a Virtual Machine (VM)?<\/h2>\n<p>A virtual machine is just like your personal computer, minus the physical parts. The machine is a software copy that contains a Virtual Processor, Memory, Storage, and Networking resources. VMs can host an operating system, but Containers cannot.<\/p>\n<p>Virtual machines are an ideal option when:<br \/>\n\u2022 You wish to have total control of the OS.<br \/>\n\u2022 Want to run custom software.<br \/>\n\u2022 Want to run custom hosting configurations.<\/p>\n<p>Think of a VM as a computer that can run Windows as well as Linux, depending on the user preference.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10243\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10243\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-10243\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Virtual-Machine-AKS.png\" alt=\"Virtual Machine AKS\" width=\"922\" height=\"520\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Virtual-Machine-AKS.png 922w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Virtual-Machine-AKS-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Virtual-Machine-AKS-768x433.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 922px) 100vw, 922px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65349997\"><\/a>Challenges of VM (Virtual Machine)<\/h2>\n<p>Virtual machines have the ability to host hundreds to thousands of workloads. The challenge with VMs is is that they are resource consumers. Imagine your personal computer <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-gb\/documentation\/\">running Windows<\/a> or Mac, and the resources it requires to boot up and stay functional. Now multiply this by the hundreds and thousands.<\/p>\n<p>Another challenge is how can you transfer the machines from one place to another? Again imagine you wish to transfer 100gb of your personal content, over the internet, to another machine. How fast will the process be? When it comes to a professional set up, apps will need to be transferred between a testing environment, pre-production, and production. This is where containers make their mark.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/04\/09\/containers-versus-virtual-machines-why-containers-are-the-winner\/hosting-workloads-in-virtual-machine-aks\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10242\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-10242\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Hosting-workloads-in-virtual-machine-AKS.png\" alt=\"Hosting workloads in virtual machine AKS\" width=\"921\" height=\"518\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Hosting-workloads-in-virtual-machine-AKS.png 921w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Hosting-workloads-in-virtual-machine-AKS-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Hosting-workloads-in-virtual-machine-AKS-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 921px) 100vw, 921px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65349998\"><\/a>Advantage of Containers<\/h2>\n<p>Containers are a great solution to solve the challenges posed by VMs.<\/p>\n<p>Imagine you wish to ship a package to a particular destination in the world. Once you place the package in a container, you can send it to just about anywhere: Asia, Africa, even Australia. Software Containers work in a similar way.<\/p>\n<p>You can package an app, place it inside a container, then send it to any destination you choose \u2013 A personal machine, a colleague\u2019s machine, a test environment, or <a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2020\/06\/16\/announcing-cloud-devops-visions-community\/\">even the cloud<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/04\/09\/containers-versus-virtual-machines-why-containers-are-the-winner\/advantages-of-using-a-container-over-a-vm\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10240\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-10240\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Advantages-of-using-a-container-over-a-VM.png\" alt=\"Advantages of using a container over a VM\" width=\"923\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Advantages-of-using-a-container-over-a-VM.png 923w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Advantages-of-using-a-container-over-a-VM-300x167.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Advantages-of-using-a-container-over-a-VM-768x428.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 923px) 100vw, 923px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65349999\"><\/a>3 Key Benefits of Containers<\/h2>\n<p>Compared to VMs, Containers offer key benefits to the user. We present the three main advantages:<br \/>\n\u2022 Enables the app to run efficiently across different computing environments.<br \/>\n\u2022 Holds everything essential to an app \u2013 from code to system tools to settings.<br \/>\n\u2022 Multiple containers are managed by a single OS, making them more lightweight than VMs.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10241\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10241\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-10241\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Container-vs-VM-Virtual-Machine.png\" alt=\"Container vs VM Virtual Machine\" width=\"918\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Container-vs-VM-Virtual-Machine.png 918w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Container-vs-VM-Virtual-Machine-300x168.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/10\/Container-vs-VM-Virtual-Machine-768x430.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 918px) 100vw, 918px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65350000\"><\/a>Summary<\/h2>\n<p>Here\u2019s a quick snapshot of how VMs compare against Containers:<\/p>\n<p>Containers carry a <a href=\"https:\/\/docs.microsoft.com\/en-gb\/documentation\/\">distinct advantage<\/a>: They are lightweight, flexible, runs on diverse environments, and most importantly, uses a secured and isolated host. Consider this statistic: Containers are expected to grow from a $2.1 billion industry to $4.3 billion in 2022.<\/p>\n<p>Virtual machines have served us well in the past. The future, however, seems to firmly belong to Containers.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Containers versus Virtual Machines: Why Containers are the Winner Introduction &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/04\/09\/containers-versus-virtual-machines-why-containers-are-the-winner\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Containers versus Virtual Machines: Why Containers are The Winner<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":10244,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[999,99,948,994,917,849],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/10208"}],"collection":[{"href